# security/{{PLATFORM}}/{{NAME}}

{{PURPOSE}}

IdP module. Seeds users with random passwords and exposes the standard IdP output set (`user_pool_id`, `app_client_id`, `app_client_secret`, `users`).

## Usage

```hcl
module "{{NAME}}" {
  source = "git::https://github.com/<org>/traefik-demo.git//security/{{PLATFORM}}/{{NAME}}?ref=vX.Y.Z"

  users = [
    { email = "demo@example.com" },
    { email = "admin@example.com" },
  ]

  redirect_uris = ["https://demo.example.com/callback"]
}
```

## Notes

- Passwords are generated by `random_password` — never hardcoded (SEC-03/04 in `/ISSUES.md` were exactly this antipattern).
- Surface them only via the `users` output, marked `sensitive = true`.

